gameFiles
Class Edge

java.lang.Object
  gameFiles.Edge
All Implemented Interfaces:
MapElement
public class Edge
extends java.lang.Object
implements MapElement

The Edge Class in ShippingGame allows creation of the connections between Nodes that Trucks can Travel along Each Edge is connected to exactly two Nodes, and the getFirstExit() and getSecondExit() methods allow access to these Nodes. Each Edge also has a length, which is the amount of time (in units that are converted to milliseconds) it takes for a Truck to cross this Edge. One useful method to highlight is the getOther(Node) method, which returns the other exit of the Edge given the first exit.

The Edge Class implements MapElement and is represented on the gui by an instance of the Road class. This implementation requires the creation of the four MapElement methods, which are relatively unused outside of the graphical representation of this Edge.

There are no public Edge constructors, so classes outside of the gameFiles package will not be able to construct additional Edge objects

The Edge Class also has two public static methods, which return the minimum and maximum lengths of all Edges, respectively.
